  <h2>Website Standards</h2>
  <hr/>
  <h3>Writing for the Web</h3>
  <p>Preferences for  punctuation and style of many commonly used words and phrases. <a href="https://pxl-elginedu.terminalfour.net/prod01/cdn-pxl-elginedu-prod/media/elginedu/cms-resources/ECC-writing-for-the-web-style-guide.pdf" title="ECC Style Guide">Download ECC style guide - PDF</a></p>

  <h3>Making Content Accessibile</h3>
  <p>Provides an overview of accessibility and covers such topics as why accessibility is important, tips for creating accessible web content, writing text to follow accessibilty guidelines, using lists within accessible content, creating accessible hyperlinks and more. <a href="https://elgin.edu/accessibility/accessible-content/" target="_blank">Learn more about accessibile content</a></p>
  
  <h3>Website Accessibility</h3>
  <p>ECC incorporates web accessibility into its development and content management processes and adheres to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0. <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/fundamentals/accessibility-intro/" title="Link leaves site. Visit w3.org/WAI/fundamentals/accessibility-intro" target="_blank">Learn more about accessibility</a></p>
  
